Class RecentKeyTreeMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
        • com.xceptance.xlt.nocoding.util.RecentKeyTreeMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>, java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>, java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>

    public class RecentKeyTreeMap
extends java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
    The map is sorted by a Comparator provided at map creation time. If the comparator finds two equal elements in the put method, it always uses the newest key, while the normal TreeMap uses the first added key. That means, if the Comparator is String.CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER and K, V are Strings, the newest capitalization of K is stored and the old one is deleted.

    ckeiner
